<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-10T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-10T13:00:00-05:00" n="157" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d157">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2766b: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Feely</hi></persName>)<note n="20" xml:id="d157fn20">The same, January 10, 1 p.m., to the Minister in
                                Paraguay as telegram No. 1.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-10T13:00:00-05:00">January 10, 1933—1
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2. [Here follows text of paragraph 1 of telegram No. 4, January 10, 1
                            p.m., to the Ambassador in Peru, printed <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.]</p>
                        <p>Please cable any information discreetly obtainable, whether this plan has
                            been discussed with the Government to which you are accredited, and
                            whether it seems likely that it meets with its approval.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>